I'd give it 5 stars if not for the priciness of it.
The food, I'm sure, is something one could find (or make themselves, if they really wanted to) elsewhere for cheaper, but the outstanding service is well worth the prices.
Vast selection of wines to go with any meal on the menu.
Although I must admit I was a tad disappointed with just a two-page selection to offer, but still the food was excellent.
