They could only accommodate  a larger group with an additional room which would increase the F&B minimum.
On top of that, I was told that they could not do a standing reception and a dinner in the same area even though when I spoke to the banquet director initial I indicated that I wanted a cocktail reception prior to the dinner.
The whole event was turning into a big mess as the F&B was going up and up.
It was very frustrating working with the banquet team.
However, when I got on site it was totally different experience.
By that time our RSVP list had grown to 80+, way more than I had expected.
Although we did expect a significant drop off, we could not count on it.
