There is a special appetizer plate that isn't even on the menu, but thanks to the Yelp photos we knew what it would look like.
Why isn't it on the menu??
It's awesome!
Olives, parmesan cheese, soprasatta, ham, and a make-your-own bruschetta with lightly grilled bread, chopped tomato & pesto mayonnaise.
I was a little disappointed at first because it seems like caprese salad is no longer on the menu, but just ask the waiter if the special appetizer is available & GET IT.
It's really good.
I got the minestrone soup & it was fine, but the highlight for me was definitely the Amatriciana pasta.
Sure, you can make pasta at home, but my pasta never came out like this!
It's slightly spicy, with *perfectly* cooked pasta & prosciutto.
If you can't decide what to get, this is a very safe choice.
The service is very attentive, and they for some reason they give you very small water glasses, which meant that our busboy had to stop by every 5 minutes & refill our water.
And this is one of those fancy places, so he covers the side of the glass facing you with a napkin as he pours water, just in case he gets a drop on your $10,000 titanium Rolex.
Just go.
The food here definitely gets an A!

